criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients with periodontitis (stage III-IV);

          -  Patients with two or more periodontal pockets in different quadrants (bleeding on
             probing (BOP)>15% and probing pocket depth (PPD) ≥5mm;

          -  More than 30 years old;

          -  Patients should have not undergone any type of periodontal therapy 6 months prior to
             initial examination.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  An uncontrolled systemic disease;

          -  Patients had antibiotic therapy during the last 3 months prior to treatment or
             nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drug use during the last 2 weeks;

          -  had periodontal treatment during last 6 months;

          -  pregnant or lactating women;

          -  allergies to the adjunct (proanthocyanidins).
